main event: A strange object was observed approximately 10 miles above the horizon moving from east to west west of Portugal on October 6, 1957. The observation lasted 3-5 minutes with no further information available.
interesting points: The sighting was of a single object, possibly a satellite or unknown aircraft, and was observed by a civilian source.
The report dismisses the possibility of the object being a balloon and states that it was definitely not Sputnik.
The object was described as high and fast, and no photographs or visual evidence of the object are included in the report.
The report was received from New York DAC, indicating that it was part of a wider system for tracking and documenting UFO sightings.
The conclusion of the report suggests that the observed object was possibly a satellite or an unknown aircraft.
sighted object: a strange object moving from east to west approximately 10 miles above the horizon
